records.addlTxt:
Defendant Arnold E Branch in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  
Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to:

COUNT 1:  9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME with 6 days credit.

COUNT 2:  90 DAYS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, CONCURRENT with Count 1.

The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*No use of alcohol, controlled substances/illegal drugs, or possession of drug paraphernalia;
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No possession of firearms;
*Obtain full time employment;
*Participate in Anger Management program;
*Perform 25 hours of community service;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The Court ordered all costs (except dna surcharge) waived due to indigency.  Defendant advised of appeal rights. 
Filed;
